Undid revision 959668583 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) Undid edits, as user was proven to be wrong about their views (see talk page discussion) and is now using an irrelevant argument to modify lead.
/* Mentions of rankings in lead */ [[User:WildlyAccurate|WildlyAccurate]] reply

[[User:Drevolt|Drevolt]], your recent edit summary takes those guidelines out of context; to be clear, rankings aren't being "used" in the lead, and no vague claim is being made here. For your reference, see the leads of other pages such as Northwestern University, Johns Hopkins, etc. The general consensus is that this is appropriate. Please take this up in talk before editing again if you still disagree (to avoid edit-warring).

Undid revision 956530122 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) I will discuss this matter further with you on the talk page, but I am reverting this edit for now based on what I previously said. You have edited the leads of several other university pages (specifically as it pertains to your misconception of boosterism) and have been consistently met with immense backlash from other editors. It thus does not make sense for your edit to prevail while we talk.

Undid revision 956528514 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) The lead of this page as well as of many other pages has been more or less the same for the past several months until you began going on a fury of changing the leads of multiple prestigious universities in the past couple of weeks. You are obviously the one who misunderstands and misrepresents Wikipedia guidelines.

Undid revision 956527572 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) After some more digging, I’ve discovered that you’ve exhibited this exact same behaviour on dozens of other university pages, including Harvard, Yale, Stanford, Columbia, Princeton, and MIT. On every occasion, several other editors greatly disagreed with you and reverted your edits, just as I am doing here. Your toxicity is childish and unwarranted. It is completely without merit.

Undid revision 956525710 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) You have a clear history of attempting to make edits related to boosterism on several university pages and being disagreed with other editors on those pages. You are evidently the one who deliberately fails to understand boosterism. In this case, it is completely neutral to leave the lead the way it is.

Undid revision 956524657 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) For anyone else who sees this, please refer to the view history of other universities including Harvard and Yale to further see how irrational Drevolt is as an editor. He should be banned.

Undid revision 956523920 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) It appears that you exhibit this same behaviour on many other university's pages. Seriously, get off Wikipedia. You are contributing nothing by incorrectly misinterpreting Wikipedia guidelines on multiple occasions and irresponsibly removing objective information.

Undid revision 956522528 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) You are correct that it contradicts the Rankings section. It is actually the Rankings section that needs to be updated; the original lead is objectively verifiable through various sources, making the wording accurate. The Rankings section cites an old source that suggests it's in the top 15. However, quick research reveals that UChicago is consistently ranked in the top 10 - so I remain firm.

Undid revision 956513213 by [[Special:Contributions/Drevolt|Drevolt]] ([[User talk:Drevolt|talk]]) Drevolt, I'm afraid you are profusely mistaken. WP:Boost warns against failing to  “describe [an academic institution] in a neutral language and verifiable facts”. It is a fact that UChicago ranks among the world’s top ten universities. Contrast this to Harvard’s profile; go take a look at their lead and see what it says: “one of the most prestigious universities in the world”.
